Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Court addresses Bail Bond Hearing. Arguments heard as to bail. Court denied bail motion for today's purposes but will hold it open until next court date

Defendant George Torres III in court.  Attorney Joseph Thomas Domask in court for George Torres III.  Attorney Abby Rockendorf appeared in court on behalf of Jon R Josephsen Jr. for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for Status Conference. Defense counsel informs court that the defendant has two new pending cases, and is further requesting an adjournment for possible resolution with all cases. Court grants request. Case adjourned for a status conference date to Br 16.
Status conference scheduled for December 19, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Case in Court for Scheduling Conference. Discussion placed on the record. Court addressed good JusticePoint Report.. Defense received discovery material and an offer from the State. Defense advised Court regarding possible Motion filing. Defense requested Status date and deadline for Motion. State did not object. Court ordered case adjourned for Status Conference. Any Motions due by October 28, 2022 end of business day. Case remains calendared in Branch 16.
